				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I didn't mean WebGL exclusively. I have not written a NES emulator but I imagine PPU emulation is CPU bound anyway, and that its output is going to be a byte array of indexed pixels. That byte array could either be converted into RGBA pixels by the CPU to load to Canvas, or (if available) take 1/4 the GPU bandwidth by loading the byte array directly via opengl. In any case proper profiling needs to be conducted before making informed optimizing decisions, and the pixel bandwidth may not even be a issue.</div>

