					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The bottleneck is in how the browser resizes canvases, not your code.<br />You can make a little test JS page that fills a canvas red and blue at 60FPS, and even that will run too slowly.<br />This is such a stunning display of incompetence from the browser makers.  In Windows, you can just make a DirectDraw surface in offscreen video memory.  Blitting a video ram surface to the primary buffer can run at around 1900FPS, and that's with stretching.</div>

					
