						<div class="postbody">I think all browsers are affected though. The problem is that canvas resizing is done through the DOM renderer, and that part of browsers has always been notoriously slow (and the main target of hate of a lot of people working with javascript, and now people doing CSS3 animations and transformations as well).<br /><br />And of course I assume they don't even care about this issue since they expect you to use WebGL and let the GPU scale it for you...</div>

